---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Project UNAC">
  <PageHero kicker="Official project statement" title="Project UNAC" lead="Project UNAC is a worldbuilding-based media mix project by SHINHWI. Its canon is released through world settings, serialized fiction, music, and visual archives, each kept as a separate but connected record." />
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container editorial-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="kicker">Architecture / canon</p>
        <h2 class="display-lg">Austere media mix</h2>
        <p class="lead">The project is built like an archive before it is built like a campaign. World files establish the rules; fiction carries time and consequence; music preserves emotional evidence; images are selected only when they add to the record.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="line-list" aria-label="Project UNAC structure">
        <article class="line-item">
          <p class="meta">01 / World settings</p>
          <h3 class="display-sm">The canon ledger</h3>
          <p class="body-copy">Locations, factions, terms, characters, and chronology are maintained as controlled entries so the setting can expand without becoming generic lore.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="line-item">
          <p class="meta">02 / Serialized fiction</p>
          <h3 class="display-sm">The reading sequence</h3>
          <p class="body-copy">Story chapters are treated as a literary archive: quiet pages, narrow measure, and chapter navigation for uninterrupted reading.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="line-item">
          <p class="meta">03 / Music divisions</p>
          <h3 class="display-sm">Originals separate from OST</h3>
          <p class="body-copy">SHINHWI Originals remain artist works under the SHINHWI catalog. Project UNAC OST remains soundtrack material tied directly to scenes, motifs, and archive events.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="line-item">
          <p class="meta">04 / Visual archive</p>
          <h3 class="display-sm">Selected figures only</h3>
          <p class="body-copy">The gallery functions as a curated register of approved visual records, not a feed and not a dump of unused production material.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
